	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />FF3j uses a TNROM board. There are no US games that use TNROM. TNROM is up to 512k PRG, 8K PRGRAM with battery backup, and 8K CHRRAM. You can convert a TKROM board to TNROM by replacing the CHRROM chip with 8K CHRRAM. I believe this is how most if not all FF3j repros are made.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


